## Powers of/uni00A0the/uni00A0Chairman and/uni00A0CEO 2.4.2

As Chairman of the Board of Directors, the Chairman and CEO organises and leads the Board's work, on whichhe reports to the Shareholders' Meeting. He oversees the proper operation of the Company's managing bodies and ensures, in particular, that the Directors are in a position to fulfil their duties. He can also request any document or information which can be used to help the Board prepare its meetings.

As ChiefExecutive Officer, the Chairman and CEO is granted full powers to act in the name of the Company under any circumstances. He/uni00A0exercises these powers within the limits of the corporate purpose and subject to the powers expressly granted by law to theShareholders' Meetings and to the Board, and within the internal limits as defined by the Board of Directors and its Internal Regulations/uni00A0 (1) .

## Limitation on/uni00A0the/uni00A0powers 2.4.3 of/uni00A0the/uni00A0Chairman and/uni00A0CEO

For internal purposes, following the decisionmade by the Board of Directors on 11/uni00A0February 2015 and in accordance with article/uni00A02 of the Board's Internal Regulations, prior to making a commitment on behalf of the Company, the Chairman and CEO must obtain prior authorisation from the Board of Directors for any significant transactions that fall outside the strategy announced by the Company, as well as the following transactions:

- carrying out acquisitions, transfers of ownership or disposals glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> of assetsand property rights and making investments for an amount exceeding €100/uni00A0million per transaction;
- signing any agreements to make investments in, or participate glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> in joint ventures with, any other French or non-French companies, except with an affiliate of Pernod Ricard (as/uni00A0defined in article/uni00A0L./uni00A0233-1 of the French Commercial Code);
- making any investments or taking any shareholding in any glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> company, partnership or investment vehicle, whether established or yet to be established, through subscription or contribution in cash or in kind, through the purchase of shares, ownership rights or other securities, and more generally in any form whatsoever, for an amount above €100/uni00A0million per transaction;
- granting loans, credits and advances exceeding €100/uni00A0million glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> per borrower, except when the borrower is an affiliate of Pernod Ricard (as defined in article/uni00A0L./uni00A0233-1 of the French Commercial Code) and/uni00A0with the exception ofloans granted for less than one year;
- borrowing, with or without granting a guarantee on corporate glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> assets, exceeding €200/uni00A0million in the same financial year, except from affiliates of Pernod Ricard (as defined in article/uni00A0L./uni00A0233-1 of the French Commercial Code), for which there is no limit;
- granting pledges, sureties or guarantees, except with express glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> delegation of authority from the Board of Directors, within the limits provided for by articles/uni00A0L./uni00A0225-35 and R./uni00A0225-28 of the French Commercial Code; and

On 27/uni00A0November 2020, the Board of Directors authorised the Chairman and CEO, for a period of one year, to grant pledges, sureties or guarantees in the name of the Company up to an overall limit of €100/uni00A0million, and for an unlimited amount to tax and customs authorities.

## Role, missions and/uni00A0reporting 2.4.4 activity of/uni00A0the/uni00A0Lead Independent Director

The Board of Directors' meeting of 23/uni00A0January 2019, on the proposition of the Nominations and Governance Committee, created a position of Lead Independent Director and entrusted it to Ms/uni00A0Patricia Barbizet.

In accordance with the Internal Regulations of the Board of Directors, the Lead Independent Director performs the following tasks:

- convenes the Board of Directors at her own initiative or in the glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> absence of the Chairman and CEO;
- is consulted on the agenda of any Board meetingsand may glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> propose any additional items on said agenda;
- chairs meetings of the Board of Directors in the absence of the glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> Chairman and CEO;
- leadsthe process of assessing the functioning of the Board of glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> Directors and reports on this evaluation to the Board;
- prevents any occurrence of conflict of interest situations; glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT>
- ensures compliance with therules of the AFEP-MEDEF Code glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> and the Board's Internal Regulations;
- convenes and chairs Executive Sessions; glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT>
- ensures that the Directors have the necessary resources to glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> carry out their duties under the best possible conditions, and that they are provided, in a reasonable manner, with the level of information appropriate to the performance of their duties;
- reviews Shareholders' requests relating to corporate glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT> governance and/uni00A0ensures that they are answered; and
- meets with the Company's investors and shareholders. glyph<c=1,font=/AAFOBE+ArialMT>

Since taking up her duties, the Lead Independent Directorhas participated, with the Executive Management, the Investor Relations and Legal Departments, in several meetings dedicated to the governance of the Company (roadshows). She has also met a large part of the teams of Pernod Ricard and some of its affiliates. Furthermore, she conducted the tri-annual assessment of the functioning of the Board of Directors, with the assistance of a specialist external firm, based in particular on individual interviews with each Directoras described in paragraph/uni00A02.6.4 below.

The Lead Independent Directorreports to the Board of Directors once a year on the performance of her duties.At Shareholders' Meetings, she/uni00A0may be invited by the Chairman and CEO to report on heractivities. It/uni00A0is/uni00A0specified that the loss of independent status would immediately terminate the functions of the Lead Independent Director.

